summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2013 GMC TERRAIN. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE VEHICLE EXPERIENCED EXCESSIVE OIL CONSUMPTION. DURING AN OIL CHANGE, THE TECHNICIAN DIAGNOSED THAT THE OIL WAS A QUART AND A HALF LOW. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO THE DEALER WHERE A TECHNICIAN PERFORMED AN OIL CONSUMPTION TEST. THE TECHNICIAN STATED THAT IT WAS WITHIN NORMAL OPERATING RANGE. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 51,155.
